prompts.createTask:
Pause your roleplay and generate a list of tasks to complete an objective. Your next response must be formatted as a numbered list of plain text entries. Do not include anything but the numbered list. The list must be prioritized in the order that tasks must be completed.

The objective that you must make a numbered task list for is: [{{objective}}].
The tasks created should take into account the character traits of {{char}}. These tasks may or may not involve {{user}} directly. Be sure to include the objective as the final task.

Given an example objective of 'Make me a four course dinner', here is an example output:
1. Determine what the courses will be
2. Find recipes for each course
3. Go shopping for supplies with {{user}}
4. Cook the food
5. Get {{user}} to set the table
6. Serve the food
7. Enjoy eating the meal with {{user}}
prompts.checkTaskCompleted:
Pause your roleplay. Determine if this task is completed: [{{task}}].
To do this, examine the most recent messages. Your response must only contain either true or false, nothing other words.
Example output:
true
prompts.currentTask: Your current task is [{{task}}]. Balance existing roleplay with completing this task.

name: SillyTavern System
mes:
Slash commands:

  1. /help – displays this help message (aliases: /?)
  2. /name (name) – sets user name and persona avatar (if set) (aliases: /persona)
  3. /sync – syncs user name in user-attributed messages in the current chat
  4. /lock – locks/unlocks a persona (name and avatar) to the current chat (aliases: /bind)
  5. /bg (filename) – sets a background according to filename, partial names allowed, will set the first one alphabetically if multiple files begin with the provided argument string (aliases: /background)
  6. /sendas – sends message as a specific character.
    Example:
    /sendas Chloe
Hello, guys!
    will send "Hello, guys!" from "Chloe".
    Uses character avatar if it exists in the characters list.
  7. /sys (text) – sends message as a system narrator
  8. /sysname (name) – sets a name for future system narrator messages in this chat (display only). Default: System. Leave empty to reset.
  9. /comment (text) – adds a note/comment message not part of the chat
  10. /single – sets the message style to single document mode without names or avatars visible (aliases: /story)
  11. /bubble – sets the message style to bubble chat mode (aliases: /bubbles)
  12. /flat – sets the message style to flat chat mode (aliases: /default)
  13. /continue – continues the last message in the chat (aliases: /cont)
  14. /go (name) – opens up a chat with the character by its name (aliases: /char)
  15. /sysgen (prompt) – generates a system message using a specified prompt
  16. /delname (name) – deletes all messages attributed to a specified name (aliases: /cancel)
  17. /send (text) – adds a user message to the chat log without triggering a generation (aliases: /add)
  18. /world – sets active World, or unsets if no args provided
  19. /dupe – duplicates the currently selected character
  20. /api (kobold, horde, novel, ooba, oai, claude, windowai, ai21) – connect to an API
  21. /impersonate - calls an impersonation response (aliases: /imp)
  22. /delchat - deletes the current chat
  23. /closechat - closes the current chat
  24. /panels - toggle UI panels on/off (aliases: /togglepanels)
  25. /vn – swaps Visual Novel Mode On/Off
  26. /newchat – start a new chat with current character (aliases: /newchat)
  27. /random – start a new chat with a random character (aliases: /random)
  28. /delmode (optional number) – enter message deletion mode, and auto-deletes N messages if numeric argument is provided (aliases: /del)
  29. /cut (requred number) – cuts the specified message from the chat
  30. /resetpanels – resets UI panels to original state. (aliases: /resetui)
  31. /bgcol – WIP test of auto-bg avg coloring
  32. /roll (dice formula) – roll the dice. For example, /roll 2d6 (aliases: /r)
  33. /show-gallery Shows the gallery (aliases: /sg)
  34. /taskcheck – checks if the current task is completed
  35. /sprite spriteId – force sets the sprite for the current character (aliases: /emote)
  36. /spriteoverride folder – sets an override sprite folder for the current character. If the name starts with a slash or a backslash, selects a sub-folder in the character-named folder. Empty value to reset to default. (aliases: /costume)
  37. /sd (argument) – requests SD to make an image. Supported arguments:

    • you – AI character full body selfie

    • face – AI character face-only selfie

    • me – user character full body selfie

    • scene – visual recap of the whole chat scenario

    • last – visual recap of the last chat message

    • raw_last – visual recap of the last chat message with no summary

    • background – generate a background for this chat based on the chat's context


    Anything else would trigger a "free mode" to make SD generate whatever you prompted.
    example: '/sd apple tree' would generate a picture of an apple tree.
  38. /idle – toggles idle mode
  39. /lockbg – locks a background for the currently selected chat (aliases: /bglock)
  40. /unlockbg – unlocks a background for the currently selected chat (aliases: /bgunlock)
  41. /autobg – automatically changes the background based on the chat context using the AI request prompt (aliases: /bgauto)
  42. /summarize – forces the summarization of the current chat using the Main API
  43. /qr - requires number argument, activates the specified QuickReply
  44. /qrset - arg: QuickReply Preset Name, swaps to that QR preset
  45. /note (text) – sets an author's note for the currently selected chat
  46. /depth (number) – sets an author's note depth for in-chat positioning
  47. /freq (number) – sets an author's note insertion frequency (aliases: /interval)
  48. /pos (chat or scenario) – sets an author's note position (aliases: /position)
